    "(40)Since the HF energy is a quadratic function of the density matrix P, E[P new (λ)] is a quadratic function of λ.",
    "Minimizing the energy by setting ∂E[P new (λ)]/∂λ = 0 leads to λ = -s/2c.",
    "However, since we fix λ to be in the domain 0≤ λ ≤ 1, if c ≤ -s/2, we should set λ = 1.Since the optimization problem has a simple analytical solution, it can be performed efficiently.",
    "To summarize, the ODA modifies the basic HF iterative step as follows:(1) Construct the mean-field Hamiltonian from the current state, i.e.",
    "Hk ≡ H HF [ Pk]."
